The paper discusses the effectiveness of neural networks in image recognition and natural language processing, which are common topics in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on the use of GPGPU technologies and libraries for accelerating mathematical routines, which falls under the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a modern C++ interface, which is relevant to the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
